     <a href="documents/WestmontCollegeInterestFreeLoanMasterPromissoryNote.pdf"></a> 
     <p><img alt="bridge" id="image19" src="uploads/2006/05/financial_aid.jpg"><br> Dear Applicant,</p> 
     <p>Your Westmont education is one of the most important and valuable investments you will ever make, and it will yield lifetime benefits. Westmont alumni have gone to the finest graduate, medical and law schools such as Stanford, Harvard, Yale and Vanderbilt. They have also accomplished their career goals by obtaining positions with top governmental agencies, with well-known businesses, in education and in the ministry. They are proof that the value gained from a Westmont education is well worth the investment.</p> 
     <p>Westmont takes great pride in providing students with academic merit, athletic, art, drama and music scholarships, grants and other types of aid that make a Westmont education possible. The admissions and financial aid offices will pay special attention to each family’s specific financial needs. We encourage all families to apply for financial aid and to give us the opportunity to “share the value” with you.</p> 
     <p>Thanks in advance for this opportunity to work with you. Please feel free to call with questions. I look forward to working with you personally.</p> 
     <p>Sincerely,</p> 
     <p>Sean Smith , Director of Financial Aid</p> 
     <p>&nbsp;</p> 
